You are a senior Flutter engineer and product-minded developer.

# 🧠 PRODUCT OVERVIEW

We are building a mobile learning application called "Learnly".

Core idea:
Users can upload or input content (PDF, image, or text), and the system transforms it into:
- Audio summaries (text-to-speech)
- Podcast-style conversations
- Flashcards
- Quiz questions

The goal is:
"Help users learn by listening, testing, and repeating."

This is NOT just a content generator.
This is a **learning experience platform**.

---

# 🔥 CORE FEATURES

1. Content Input
- Text input
- PDF upload (future-ready)
- Image OCR (future-ready)

2. AI Outputs
- Audio Summary
- Podcast
- Flashcards
- Quiz

3. Learning Loop
- Listen → Understand → Test → Retain

4. Shareability (IMPORTANT)
- Users can mark generated content as:
  - Private
  - Public
- Public content can be explored by other users
- Users can share their generated learning content

---

# 🎯 MVP SCOPE (STRICT)

Focus ONLY on:
- Text input
- Audio summary (mocked or placeholder)
- Basic quiz (mock data)
- Basic flashcards (mock data)
- Private/Public toggle (UI only)
- Share button (UI only)
- Search bar for public content (UI only)

DO NOT implement:
- Real backend
- Authentication
- Payments
- Complex state persistence

---

# 🏗️ ARCHITECTURE

Use Feature-Based Architecture:

lib/
  core/
  features/
    home/
    upload/
    processing/
    player/
    quiz/
    flashcards/
  shared/

---

# ⚙️ STATE MANAGEMENT

- Use Riverpod
- Keep state simple
- Avoid over-engineering

---

# 🎨 UI PRINCIPLES

- Clean and modern
- Minimal cognitive load
- Fast interactions
- Mobile-first UX

---

